# FS25_FieldToDoList - Project Rules

## Release and Build

- Keep `modDesc.xml` version unchanged unless the user explicitly requests a release bump.
- Preferred local build command: `python3 tools/generate_assets.py && ./build.sh`.
- After mod updates, do a full FS25 restart.

## Maintainer shell (fish)

- **Maintainer uses fish**, not bash — do **not** suggest bash-only syntax (`$(cat <<'EOF' … EOF)`, `source <(…)`).
- For git commits, prefer a **single `-m "…"`** line or fish-safe multi-line strings; example:

```fish
git commit -m "Release 0.1.0.4: short summary.

Optional second paragraph in the same string."
```

- Copy-paste blocks in docs/PR instructions may show bash; note that fish users must adapt redirection/heredocs themselves (see `CONTRIBUTING.md`).

## Lua / Scripting (FS25)

- **Do not use `goto` / labels** (`::label::`) in mod Lua — the Giants runtime is Lua 5.1-style and does not support them; the script file may fail to load and break entire features (e.g. empty field list).
- Use normal control flow instead: `if`/`else`, nested loops, helper functions, or `continue`-style `if` blocks inside loops.

## Save and Runtime Safety

- Do not read `savegame*/fields.xml` at runtime (`FieldSavegameReader.ENABLE_DISK_READ = false` — Proton can truncate the file on io.open).
- If save overlay is ever re-enabled, only via `FieldSavegameReader` with strict one-shot cache and save/load guards.
- Avoid repeated/looped file reads in menu/update paths; prefer live `FieldState` / engine data.
- Avoid SCS field-map loops in menu/update paths (`buildFieldMap`/`enumerateFields`).
- Keep deferred startup reads (`deferReadsUntilGameplay`) to avoid load deadlocks.

## Performance (Field Overview Scan)

- **Two update paths (do not merge):**
  - **Overview scan** — all owned fields for the ESC table (incremental, heavier). Runs on menu open and optional periodic full rescan.
  - **Task auto-complete** — only fields with open trackable field tasks (`updateAutoCompletion`, ~1 s). Uses live probes + fingerprint cache; independent of the overview queue.
- When auto-complete marks a field task done, **refresh that field row only** via `refreshFieldRecordSync(fieldId)` — do not wait for the 5 s rescan or a full cache invalidate.
- Field overview uses **incremental scan** (`ToDoManager` + `FieldScanner.collectOwnedFieldCandidates()`), not a synchronous full `scanOwnedFields()` on every menu refresh.
- **Overview grid** uses `OVERVIEW_SAMPLE_GRID_STEPS` (3); **completion / auto-complete** keeps full grid (5). Do not raise overview grid without measuring.
- **Probe aggregation** may use short TTL cache (`PROBE_AGGREGATION_CACHE_TTL_MS`); refresh center/harvest from live center probe on cache hit.
- **Scan pacing:** `OWNED_FIELDS_SCAN_BATCH_SIZE` (5), `OWNED_FIELDS_SCAN_INTERVAL_MS` (40), `OWNED_FIELDS_CACHE_MS` (4000). Advance via `ToDoManager:tickOwnedFieldsScan(dt, 2)` while the menu tab is open (`setOwnedFieldsScanActive(true)` on open, `false` on close) — up to **2 batches per frame** (~10 fields per tick at default). UI sync runs from **`InGameMenu.update`** (and mission-update fallback) calling `FieldToDoMenuFrame:onFrameUpdate` — custom tab pages do not receive frame updates from the engine alone.
- **UI refresh during scan:** on batch progress call `fieldList:reloadData()` — **`reloadVisibleItems()` does not reliably update** cell text when `...` placeholders become real values.
- **`deferredListReload` must call `refreshLists(false)`** — never invalidate the owned-fields cache on the 500 ms poll (that reset the scan every tick and blocked gradual fill-in).
- **Passive refresh while menu open:** full invalidate at most every `OWNED_FIELDS_MENU_RESCAN_MS` (15 s default) — enough for fields without open tasks. Fields with auto-complete tasks refresh via `refreshFieldRecordSync` on completion.
- **No vanilla “field worked” event** — plow/mow while menu open on a field *without* a task waits for the periodic rescan or menu re-open. Engine hooks: `MessageType.FINISHED_GROWTH_PERIOD` (daily growth) and `MessageType.FARMLAND_OWNER_CHANGED` → `markOwnedFieldsOverviewStale()` (immediate rescan if tab open).
- First paint: all owned field rows appear immediately with placeholders (`pendingScan`, columns `...`); values replace placeholders batch by batch.
- **Scan indicator:** yellow blinking dot (●) next to „Feldübersicht“ while scan runs; solid green when complete. Tooltip shows progress (`ftdl_scan_status_scanning`).
- Scan start/complete: one `FieldToDoLog.info` line each (visible in `log.txt`).
- Task adopt on pending row: `refreshFieldRecordSync(fieldId)` before `addTaskFromFieldAction`.
- Debug / `ftdlAll`: `getOwnedFields(true)` for synchronous full scan only.
- **Auto-complete:** group tasks by `fieldId`; reuse completion ratios via fingerprint cache; always refresh coverage (plow/sow) polygon queries even when fingerprint matches.

## UI and To-Do Behavior

- To-do ordering is based on `sortIndex` (user order), not work-order presets.
- Keep moved task selected after Up/Down; clear selection after delete.
- Guard SmoothList reload selection (`ignoreTaskSelectionChanged`) and sync by task id, not row index.
- Keep mini up/down buttons as arrow icons (↑/↓) with localized tooltips (`Hoch` / `Runter`); no drag-and-drop.

## HUD and Logging

- HUD shows manual tasks only (`getManualTasksForDisplay()`), max 5 open tasks.
- Keep HUD simple (plain panel, no settings line in HUD).
- In `InGameMenuIntegration`, use `Logging.info`/`Logging.warning`; avoid `print()`.

## Task and Advisor Rules

- Open tasks render above completed tasks.
- Completed tasks capped at 10; newest completed goes to top of completed group.
- `moveTask` must not cross open/completed boundaries.
- While `isWithered`, keep plow and roller incomplete in auto-complete checks.
- For organic mode display, use `getWorkOrderDisplayLabel()` (not preset label).
- Field classification must be multi-layered (`arable` / `grass` / `bare_soil` / `unknown`) and based on **multiple in-field probes**, not a single center sample.
- Prefer probe aggregation + dominant situation in overview labels/suggestions (`aggregateFieldProbes` + representative state), with center probe as tie-breaker.
  - **Harvest month uses the field center probe** (`aggregation.harvestState` = center) — not max-growth edges (maize silage → Jul) and not min-growth edge strips (growth 0 / missing fruit → „Wächst“ with no prognosis).
- Never use a blind default-grass fallback on bare worked soil: on `PLOWED`/`CULTIVATED`/`SEEDBED` without active crop, show crop as `-` and do not collapse to grass.
- Specific grass crops (Luzerne/Klee/Alfalfa): keep localized fruit name even when `fieldHasPartialSoilWork` — do not collapse to generic „Gras (teilw. bearb.)“ when probes resolved a non-generic index.
- Plow recommendation must align with completion logic: `PLOWED` + `needsPlowing == false` means plowing done (ignore stale `plowLevel > 0` alone).
- Grass/meadow post-mow handling: if `isCut`, do **not** suggest mow again; show regrowth / harvest-window and follow-up logistics (swath/collect/bale).
- For harvest readiness (vanilla + mod fruits), rely on `FruitTypeDesc` growth APIs (`getIsHarvestable`, `getIsHarvestReady`, `getIsCut`, `getIsGrowing`, `getIsWithered`) with min/max harvesting-state fallback.
- **Harvest month (Ernte-Spalte / Vorschlag):**
  - FS25 season period (1..12) ≠ calendar month — map via `getCalendarMonthForSeasonPeriod` (period 5=Jul, 8=Okt, …).
  - Dual-window crops (maize): `getIsHarvestableInPeriod` is true from **July** (silage/forage, growth ~5) and again in **autumn** (grain, growth 7 `getIsHarvestReady`). UI must use **`isFruitPrimaryHarvestInPeriod`** (projected growth + `getIsHarvestReady`), not the first harvestable period alone.
  - ETA steps target **`minHarvestingGrowthState`** when `getIsHarvestReady` exists (grain-ready), not `maxHarvestingGrowthState` (may include dead/withered).
  - Always pass **`aggregation.harvestState`** (via `resolveHarvestFieldState`) into harvest-window helpers — not `representativeState`.
- Grass residue flow must distinguish `loose` vs `swath` vs `baled` vs `none` from live map data (`DensityMapHeightUtil` + windrow fill levels), not a single generic grass-rest state.
- **Grass residue detection (`detectGrassResidue` + `fuseGrassResidueSignals`):**
  - Scan: cross (E–W, N–S) + diagonal bars through field center (~85 probe points active).
  - Signals: windrow liters (`DensityMapHeightUtil`), engine height (`getDensityHeightAtWorldPos`), fill-type at point (`getDensityTypeIndexAtWorldPos`), `stubbleShredLevel`, field bales.
  - Fusion: **never default to `loose`** without positive material; cut + no signal → `none` (Nachwuchs only). `swath` from sparse line hits, windrow fill-type, or shred. `loose` only from dense scattered coverage.
  - Proton: `DensityMapHeightUtil` global may be nil — use engine height/fill-type fallbacks; do not treat unavailable map as empty loose pile.
- Post-mow suggestions must follow residue state:
  - `loose` -> `grass_swath`
  - `swath` -> show all three options (`grass_collect`/Ladewagen, `grass_bale`, `grass_silage_bale`)
  - `baled` -> `grass_bale_collect`.
- Auto-completion for grass logistics must use the same residue/bale signals as suggestions (no separate heuristic branch).
- Bale follow-up is field-local: count only bales physically inside the field polygon.
- Weed done rule: if dead/sprayed weeds exist on field probes and live weed coverage is <= 5%, treat weed tasks as done (no new weed combat/watch suggestion).
- **Weed detection details:**
  - `WEED_STATE_DEAD_MIN = 6` (FS25 `weed.xml`: states 0–5 alive/sprayed-visible, **6+ dead** — state 6 „small dead“ is not live).
  - When `weedSummary.total > 0`, **coverage wins** for display, suggestions, auto-complete, and progress — do not let center `isWeedDeadOrSprayed` override live coverage (or vice versa).
  - `sampleWeedCoverage`: count dead vs live **mutually exclusive** per probe (`isWeedProbeDead` first, then live only if not dead).
  - `FieldTaskCompletion` weed tasks: if coverage exists, complete only via `isWeedTaskDoneByCoverage`.

## Debug (Proton-friendly)

- Manual only: **F9** (or LCtrl+F9) → `FieldDebugConsole` / `ftdlDump <id>`, `ftdlAll`, `ftdlHelp`. **No auto-dump** on menu open, save load, or row click.
- Log tag: `[FS25_FieldToDoList] DUMP` in `log.txt`.
- Useful dump lines: `weedCoverage`, `harvestState` vs `representativeState`, `getHarvestWindowHint`, `harvestProjection`.
- `FSDensityMapUtil` may be **nil as global** under Proton — fruit/weed still work via `FieldState` probes; do not rely on density-map globals in menu paths.
- If dump and UI disagree on Ernte month: compare center/harvestState growth vs representative (max-growth) probe.

## Validation Focus (Field Overview)

- Regression-check every advisor refactor with representative saves:
  - freshly plowed empty field must not render as grass (e.g. Field 14 class of bug),
  - mown lucerne/alfalfa must not suggest mow again (show regrowth/next window); label must stay **Luzerne**, not „Gras (teilw. bearb.)“,
  - harvest-ready cereals (e.g. wheat) must be flagged harvest-ready in overview,
  - grass logistics chain must be consistent (`loose` -> `swath` -> collect/bale -> bale_collect),
  - **Körnermais** early season (center growth=1, April): Ernte **Okt**, not Jul (silage window),
  - **sprayed wheat** with dead weed probes (e.g. Field 9): Unkraut **tot**, no combat/watch suggestion when live coverage <= 5%.
